# DRONE-DOMINANCE — Full UAS encounter lifecycle (friendly fleet → hostile fuse → engage → AAR)
# Copy to .env (or rely on the repo-root .env). The shared kamiwaza_client
# auto-detects the active provider in this priority:
#   1. KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL    (Kamiwaza on-prem)        ← CUAS decisions stay in the SCIF
#   2. OPENROUTER_API_KEY   (OpenRouter)
#   3. LLM_BASE_URL + LLM_API_KEY (any OpenAI-compat)
#   4. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY    (Anthropic)
#   5. OPENAI_API_KEY       (OpenAI direct)

# === On-prem Kamiwaza (the recommended posture for any CUAS workflow) ===
# KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL=https://kamiwaza.local/api/v1
# KAMIWAZA_API_KEY=...

# === OpenAI direct (default for the demo; vision-capable) ===
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# === Real-data ingestion (optional) ===
# Plug-in points are documented in data/load_real.py:
#   • Drone Dataset (UAV)            — Kaggle visual photos     → REAL_VISUAL_DIR
#   • HIT-UAV                        — thermal IR frames        → REAL_THERMAL_DIR
#   • DroneRF-B Spectra              — RF spectrogram tiles     → REAL_RF_SPECTRA_DIR
#   • Drone RC RF Identification     — controller signatures    → REAL_RC_CSV
#   • Xperience-10M                  — egocentric helmet stills → REAL_XPERIENCE_DIR

# === Model overrides (optional) ===
# LLM_PRIMARY_MODEL=gpt-5.4-mini
# LLM_FALLBACK_MODELS=gpt-5.4-mini,gpt-4o-mini,gpt-4o
# DRONE_DOMINANCE_HERO_MODEL=gpt-5.4
# DRONE_DOMINANCE_VISION_MODEL=gpt-4o
